defaultIn 2010 there were an estimated 35.6 million people with Alzheimer’s disease and other dementias worldwide.
default  This number will 
defaultincrease to 66 million by the year 2015 and 
defaultwill rise to 135 million
default by 2050.  The main increase will be in low and middle income countries where more than 70% of people with dementia will live by 2050 (Figure 1).
