default average life expectancy for women increas
defaultes, especially among the “oldest old” group, more women are at risk of dementia
default 
default but a paradox exists because although women are living longer, they are living with more disabilities stemming from dementia
default 
default. Not only are the numbers not in women’s favo
defaultur
default, 
default 
default research indicates women decline at faster speeds than men regarding cognitive functions
default.  Because dementia
default is expected to triple by 2050, women will be affected in
default other ways, 
defaultas they become primary caregivers for love
defaultd ones
default, resulting in
default decreased p
defaultarticipation in the workforce and
default a loss in wages 
default. In fact, a majority of total costs from dementia derive from informal, usually unpaid care provided by spouses, daughters
default, and daughters-in-law 
default.
default 
default Women are in jeopardy particularly because of gender dis
defaultparities as more women are less educated, face higher poverty rates, and are valued less in certain societies. This is of concern especially in developing countries which intensify the disparities and inequalities women currently face and will continue to 
defaultexperience unless
default persistent action is taken at
default national and global level
defaults by declaring dementia
default a woman’
defaults health issue.
