default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe G8 meeting on dementia in London has issued a declaration identifying dementia as a major disease burden and has resolved to increa
defaultse significantly the resources devoted to dementia resource.
default This is greatly welcomed. But if dementia is to be, in the Prime Minister’s words, at the heart of the future development agenda then the UK needs to give a lead through its own development progr
defaultamme.
default 
default The meeting also resolved to support countries to strengthen health and social care systems to improve care and services for people with dementia.  This is something that can begin to have a more immediate impact as opposed to the long term impact o
defaultf more and better research.
