default5.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAlzheimer’s Disease International (ADI) was created in 1984 by the Alzheimer societies of the UK, 
defaultCanada, USA and Australia to be the global voice on dementia and exchange information betwee
defaultn societies worldwide.  
defaultIt
default 
defaulthas 
default 80 member organisations from all parts of the world. Al
defaultl
default members are the leading patient and family organisations in their countries
default. There 
defaultare
default currently a number of associations from Africa and the Middle East seeking support and once they are established they w
defaultill become members
default in the next few years.
default  It is headquartered in London.
default5.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe 10/66 Dementia Research 
defaultGroup
default was formed in 199
default8 in India and is led by a research group from the Institute of Psychiatry, King’s College London. This group has done ground-breaking community based research in lower and middle-inco
defaultme countries
default into the prevalence and incidence of dementia, risk factors
default and social systems and
default has
default published over 60 scientific papers into the main international scientific journals. This included a series of five World Alzheimer Reports published with ADI since the year 2009 and the data from these reports are now the leadi
defaultng sources of information on dementia worldwide.
default5.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAlzheimer’s Society is the leading dementia charity in the UK, operating in England, Wales and Northern Ireland.  It has long established
default dementia support services 
defaultand leads a multi-million pound dementia 
defaultresearch funding programme
default primarily
default within the UK.  It has been credited with raising awareness of dementia to the extent that in 2007 the government made dementia a health priority and became the leading partner in the National Dementia Strategy.  It is 
defaultworking closely with the Prime Minister’s Challenge on dementia and is in the forefront of the work to create dementia friendly communities
default.
